s-grc1:57\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Hp.\">Hp.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Art.\">Art.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">57</biblScope></bibl></cit>, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0014.tlg020.perseus-grc1:7\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ D.\">D.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">20.7</biblScope></bibl>. </sense> <sense n=\"4\" id=\"n104163.5\" level=\"3\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> sts. at the beginning of a speech, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ἐγὼ μὲν τ</foreign>. . . , referring to something present to the minds of the speaker and hearer, <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">now</tr_> I . . , <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0032.tlg006.perseus-grc1:5:1:2\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ X.\">X.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ An.\">An.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">5.1.2</biblScope></bibl>, cf. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0032.tlg007.perseus-grc1:6:2:14\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Cyr.\">Cyr.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">6.2.14</biblScope></bibl>. </sense> <sense n=\"5\" id=\"n104163.6\" level=\"3\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> with <mood opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"mood\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ subj.\">subj.</a></mood> of exhortation or imper., in signfs. <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0032.tlg007.perseus-grc1:1\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">1</biblScope></bibl>,<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0032.tlg007.perseus-grc1:2\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">2</biblScope></bibl>,<bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0032.tlg007.perseus-grc1:3\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">3</biblScope></bibl>, <forei